  "summary": "string-formatter-pro exfiltrates cloud instance metadata on install",
  "details": "The package's postinstall lifecycle script runs on `npm install` and issues curl requests to cloud instance-metadata endpoints (AWS/Alibaba/Tencent at 169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/), then POSTs the collected metadata and a /data directory listing to the hardcoded host pwpzhsrbtvmfqrqr7onqcwnrcii960up.oastify.com (a Burp Collaborator OAST subdomain). The package's advertised functionality is a single one-line `capitalize` export, with no legitimate purpose served by the install-time network activity. Cloud instance metadata endpoints frequently return temporary IAM credentials on affected hosts, making this a credential-exfiltration vehicle disguised as a string utility.",
